rischen Falls bietet die vorliegende Untersuchung einen umfassenden Überblick über den monastischen Schreibbetrieb und wichtige Erkenntnisse zur mittelalterlichen Schriftkultur und zum Kloster als Ort literarischer Kultur. Mit einem Vorwort von Nigel F. Palmer.  aThe Dominican nuns of St. Katharina’s convent in Saint Gall dedicated themselves especially to their library and the production of manuscripts in the convent’s own scriptorium. Based on this exemplary case, the present study provides a comprehensive overview of monastic text production and gives important insights into the culture of medieval writing and the convent as a place of literary culture.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aDominican sisterszSwitzerlandvSaint GallvHistory. 0aDominican sisterszSwitzerlandzSaint GallxHistory. 0aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINESvLibrary & Information SciencevArchives & Special Libraries. 0aManuscripts, MedievalzSwitzerlandvSaint GallvCatalogs. 0aManuscripts, MedievalzSwitzerlandzSaint GallvCatalogs. 0aMonastic librarieszSwitzerlandvSaint GallvHistory. 0aMonastic librarieszSwitzerlandzSaint GallxHistory. 0aScribeszSwitzerlandvSaint GallvHistory. 0aScribeszSwitzerlandzSaint GallxHistory. 0aScriptoriazSwitzerlandvSaint GallvHistory. 0aScriptoriazSwitzerlandzSaint GallxHistory. 4aFrauenforschung. 4aFrauenkloster. 4aKlosterbibliothek. 4aSchreibende Frauen. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aConvent.  amonastic library.  awomen's studies.  awriting women.1 aPalmer, Nigel F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMP